President Muhammadu Buhari has admitted that fighting corruption in his government is a hard nut to crack.  The President disclosed that despite the challenges, his administration ensures that those who hold public offices and are found guilty of corruption are shown the door without much publicity. Nigeria's President Muhammadu Buhari. Buhari said this during the live interview he granted the Arise News TV monitored by SaharaReporters on Thursday.  “Corruption is very difficult under this system. But, I will not change. Whenever we have an intelligence of anyone that is being accountable, we ease him out. We don’t give too much publicity,” Buhari said.